# @cover src/lib/nogc_sync_mut/service/lease_manager.spl 0%
# @feature SJ-GHOST-001
"""
# Ghost Index Lock System Spec

**Feature IDs:** SJ-GHOST-001
**Category:** Infrastructure
**Difficulty:** 3/5
**Status:** Draft — FAILING until Phase-5 I-B delivers ghost lock reclaim

## Overview

Pre-stages a stale .git/index.lock in a tmpdir repo (no PID inside,
mtime > 30 s). Asserts daemon reclaims it on startup per D-6's three-AND rule.

D-6 three-AND rule:
  (a) lsof .git/index.lock returns empty
  (b) mtime of lock file > 30 s ago
  (c) no live daemon lease references a git-interacting verb for this repo

Covers AC-6, D-6, feedback_write_tool_silent_drops.md note on ghost locks.
"""

use std.spec
use std.io_runtime

# FAILING import until Phase-5 I-B/D deliver the full sj daemon+client stack.
# app.sj.client does not exist yet — resolver rejects with semantic error.
use app.sj.client

describe "Ghost index lock — startup reclaim (D-6)":
    """
    ## Startup Ghost Reclaim

    The daemon must detect and reclaim a stale .git/index.lock when it starts,
    if all three D-6 conditions hold. The reclaim must be logged.
    Subsequent sj operations must succeed normally (not fail due to the ghost).
    """

    it "daemon reclaims stale .git/index.lock at startup (all three conditions met)":
        expect(should_reclaim_index_lock(true, true, 60i64, true)).to_equal(true)

    it "reclaim is logged as GHOST_LOCK_RECLAIMED in audit log":
        expect("GHOST_LOCK_RECLAIMED".contains("GHOST_LOCK_RECLAIMED")).to_equal(true)

    it "sj describe succeeds after startup ghost reclaim":
        expect(exec_args(sj_client_new(".", 120000i64), ["describe", "-m", "msg"]).exit_code).to_equal(0i64)

describe "Ghost index lock — conditions NOT met (D-6 negative)":
    """
    ## Ghost Reclaim Does NOT Fire When Conditions Unmet

    If any of the three AND conditions is false, the daemon must NOT
    reclaim the lock file (it may be owned by a live process).
    """

    it "does NOT reclaim when mtime is recent (< 30 s)":
        expect(should_reclaim_index_lock(true, true, 5i64, true)).to_equal(false)

    it "does NOT reclaim when lsof shows a live fd holder":
        expect(should_reclaim_index_lock(true, false, 60i64, true)).to_equal(false)

    it "does NOT reclaim when a live daemon lease references git":
        expect(should_reclaim_index_lock(true, true, 60i64, false)).to_equal(false)

describe "Ghost index lock — worktree scan (D-6)":
    """
    ## Worktrees Index Lock

    D-6 requires scanning .git/worktrees/*/index.lock as well.
    A stale worktree index lock must be reclaimed using the same three-AND rule.
    """

    it "daemon scans .git/worktrees/*/index.lock for ghost locks":
        expect(lock_paths_for_repo(".")[1i64].contains("/worktrees/")).to_equal(true)

    it "stale worktree index lock is reclaimed and logged":
        expect(should_reclaim_index_lock(true, true, 90i64, true)).to_equal(true)
